    • skipOverAny

      public static ImPair<String,String> skipOverAny(char charToSkipOver, String stringToParse)

      Skip over any characters at the start of stringToParse that are == to charToSkipOver 

      
 ("xx", "y") == skipOverAny('x', "xxy")
 ("", "y")   == skipOverAny('x', "y")
 ("", "")    == skipOverAny('x', "")
 ("", "")    == skipOverAny('x', "xxx")

    • splitAt

      public static ImPair<String,String> splitAt(char charToSplitAt, String stringToParse)

      return the prefix and suffix of the first occurrence of charToSplitAt in stringToParse or null if stringToParse does not contain charToSplitAt 

      
 ("ab", "c")     == splitAt('/', "ab/c")
 ("abc", "")     == splitAt('/', "abc/")
 ("", "abc")     == splitAt('/', "/abc")
 ("abc", null)   == splitAt('/', "abc")

    • splitAt

      public static ImPair<String,String> splitAt(String separator, String stringToParse)

      Return a ImPair containing the prefix and suffix of the first occurrence of separator in stringToParse or a ImPair with null , stringToParse if stringToParse does not contain separator 

      
 ("ab", "c")     == splitAt('/', "ab/c")
 ("abc", "")     == splitAt('/', "abc/")
 ("", "abc")     == splitAt('/', "/abc")
 (null, "abc")   == splitAt('/', "abc")
 (null, "" )     == splitAt('/', "")

    • getStringFromVnf

      public static ImPair<String,String> getStringFromVnf(String stringToParse)

      Assume there is a vnf representation of a string at the start of stringToParse and return the string and the rest of stringToParse 

      
 ("ab", "") == getStringFromVnf( "2 ab")
 ("abc", "def") == getStringFromVnf('/', "3 abcdef")
